                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-05-26</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The shortcomings of Doniger's general Indological scholarship have been detailed by Michael Witzel and Rajiv Malhotra. This book suffers from the same flaws. The translations are idiosyncratic, and she is obsessed with finding sex, even in situations that none is called for.</span>
                  
              
